spanishExample: Solo lee historias cortas.
englishTranslation: She only reads short stories.

spanishExample: El tiempo está frío y seco.
englishTranslation: The weather is cold and dry.

spanishExample: Ese edificio antiguo debe ser caro.
englishTranslation: That old building must be expensive.

spanishExample: Siempre leo lo que él haya escrito.
englishTranslation: I always read whatever he has written.

spanishExample: Escríbele antes del sábado.
englishTranslation: Write to him before Saturday.

spanishExample: Tienes que almorzar ahora mientras la comida está caliente.
englishTranslation: You have to eat lunch now while the food is hot.

spanishExample: Octubre fue un mes mojado, espero que marzo sea mejor.
englishTranslation: October was a wet month; I hope March is better.

spanishExample: La ropa rosa es ancha.
englishTranslation: The pink clothes are wide.

spanishExample: Tienes que aprender a leer antes de mayo.
englishTranslation: You have to learn to read before May.

spanishExample: Lo leí despacio en abril.
englishTranslation: I read it slowly in April.

spanishExample: Quiero cenar comida fresca, no quiero que esté tibia.
englishTranslation: I want to have fresh food for dinner; I don’t want it to be lukewarm.

spanishExample: El amarillo está sucio, ¿puedes cambiarlo por el marrón?
englishTranslation: The yellow one is dirty; can you exchange it for the brown one?

spanishExample: Cuando viaje en la primavera, compraré un teléfono barato.
englishTranslation: When I travel in the spring, I’ll buy a cheap phone.

spanishExample: Aprendí que ella no cena los lunes.
englishTranslation: I learned that she doesn’t have dinner on Mondays.

spanishExample: Desayuné con un plato limpio.
englishTranslation: I had breakfast with a clean plate.

spanishExample: Siempre almuerzo a las dos los viernes.
englishTranslation: I always have lunch at two on Fridays.

spanishExample: La próxima estación será verano; no puedo esperar hasta junio.
englishTranslation: Next season it’ll be Summer; I can’t wait until June.

spanishExample: Escribe la carta antes del jueves 3 de enero.
englishTranslation: Write the letter before Thursday, January 3.

spanishExample: No quiero que viaje en tren, es lento.
englishTranslation: I don’t want her to travel by train; it’s slow.

spanishExample: Lo ha aprendido en solo un rato.
englishTranslation: She has learned it in just a little while.

spanishExample: El auto gris es demasiado estrecho.
englishTranslation: The gray car is too narrow.

spanishExample: Nos vemos el martes 2 de noviembre.
englishTranslation: I’ll see you on Tuesday, November 2.

spanishExample: Sé que es tu color favorito, pero no todo tiene que ser violeta.
englishTranslation: I know it’s your favorite color, but not everything has to be violet.
